# HTML

HyperText Markup Language

---

# syntax

```
opening tag <element>
content
closing tag </element>
```

1. element : tag name
   - <p> paragraph of text
   - ~~<a> anchor~~
2. tag
   - <elememt>
   - </elememt>
3. HTML attribute

   modifies how an element behaves
   - <a href="">

## syntax of attribute set

attribute set: modifies different parts of elememt's behavior

<TagName AttributeName1="value1" AttributeName2="value2">

## quirk of HTML
- extra spaces or new lines are ignored
- generally two spaces per indent in HTML&CSS



- dot .
- dash -
- less than <
- greater than >
- slash /
- double qoutes "
- underscore _
